record_data.record_title: Reactive Power Rate Schedule FERC No. 13
record_data.record_plain_text: ALLEGHENY ENERGY SUPPLY COMPANY, LLC Rate Schedule FERC No. 13 Reactive Power and Voltage Control from Generation Sources Service Allegheny Energy Supply Company, LLC ("AE Supply"), on behalf of Buchanan Generation, LLC, provides Reactive Power and Voltage Control from Generation Sources Service ("Reactive Power") from a natural gas-ftred generating facility located in Buchanan County, Virginia within the control area administered by the PJM Interconnection, L.L.C. ("PJM") in order to assist in maintaining transmission voltages within acceptable limits on the PJM transmission system. This rate schedule sets forth AE Supply's revenue requirements for the provision of Reactive Power, as contemplated by the revised Schedule 2 of the PJM Open Access Transmission Tariff, filed in Docket No. ER00-3327-000, which provides that PJM will pay generation owners their monthly revenue requirement for Reactive Power. REVENUE REQUIREMENT Generation Facility Monthly Revenue Requirement Buchanan 1 $7,853.47 Buchanan 2 $7,650.79 Total Monthly Revenue Requirement $15,504.26 Total Annual $186,051.12 EFFECTIVE DATES This Rate Schedule FERC No. 13 shall be effective from January 3, 2018 until February 28, 2018.
